extreme gradient boosting decision trees (XGBoost) were used for landslide susceptibility assessment (Song et al., 2020). Although the ensemble learning method has better performance in landslide mappings than the single machine learning model, it requires much more extra time of computation and is more difÔ¨Åcult to manipulate, limiting its wide use.
Although some easy-to-use machine learning tools, such as Scikitlearn library (in Python) and Waikato Environment for Knowledge Analysis software, have been proposed (Eibe et al., 2016; Pedregosa et al., 2011), there are other major challenges to use machine learning

